Q
\|Q x\| = \|x\|
A
\lambda_{\text{min}} \|x\|^2 \le \langle x, Ax \rangle \le \lambda_{\text{max}} \|x\|^2
A = Q \Lambda Q^T
Q
\Lambda = \operatorname{diag}(\lambda_1,...,\lambda_n)
\langle x, Ax \rangle = \langle Q^Tx, \Lambda (Q^Tx) \rangle = \sum_k \lambda_k [Q^Tx]_k^2
\lambda_{\text{min}} \sum_k  [Q^Tx]_k^2 \le \langle x, Ax \rangle \le \lambda_{\text{max}} \sum_k  [Q^Tx]_k^2 
\sum_k  [Q^Tx]_k^2 = \|Q^T x\|^2 = \|x\|^2
